Multiple regression model

health_indicators <- read.csv("~/Desktop/Data Visualization/COVID19/All_data_short.csv", header=TRUE, stringsAsFactors =TRUE)

regression1 <- lm(Death_density ~ CHE_PercentGDP + Doctor_density + Provider_density + Hospital_bed_density, data = health_indicators)
summary(regression1)

Creating Bubble Chart

# Load libraries
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
# Load dataset
health_indicators <- read.csv("~/Desktop/Data Visualization/COVID19/All_data_short.csv", header=TRUE, stringsAsFactors =TRUE)

# Plot
p <- ggplot(health_indicators, aes(x = CHE_PercentGDP, y = Hospital_bed_density, size = Death_density))
p + geom_point(color = "DarkBlue", alpha = 0.6) +
  ggtitle("Health System Readiness Indicators and COVID19 Deaths") +
  theme_light() +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) +
  theme(text = element_text(family = "Times New Roman")) +
  theme(legend.position = c(0.9, 0.85), legend.background = element_rect(fill = NA)) +
  labs(x = "Health Expenditures as % of GDP", y = "Doctors per 100k Population", color = "Deaths per 100k Population")

Basic Scatter Plot

library(ggplot2)

health_indicators <- read.csv("~/Desktop/Data Visualization/COVID19/All_data_short.csv", header=TRUE, stringsAsFactors =TRUE)

p <- ggplot(health_indicators, mapping = aes(CHE_PercentGDP, Death_density))
p + geom_point(color = "DarkGreen") +
  labs(x = "Current Per Capita Health Expenditures as % GDP", y = "COVID19 Deaths per 100k Population") +
  ggtitle("Per Capita Health Expenditures and COVID19 Deaths") + 
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) +
  scale_x_continuous() +
  theme(text = element_text(family = "Helvetica"))

p <- ggplot(health_indicators, mapping = aes(Doctor_density, Death_density))
p + geom_point(color = "Blue") +
  labs(x = "Medical Doctors per 100k Population", y = "COVID19 Deaths per 100k Population") +
  ggtitle("Density of Medical Doctors and COVID19 Deaths") + 
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) +
  scale_x_continuous() +
  theme(text = element_text(family = "Helvetica"))

p <- ggplot(health_indicators, mapping = aes(Provider_density, Death_density))
p + geom_point(color = "Orange") +
  labs(x = "Healthcare Providers per 100k", y = "COVID19 Deaths per 100k Population") + ggtitle("Density of Healthcare Providers and COVID19 Deaths") + 
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) +
  scale_x_continuous() +
  theme(text = element_text(family = "Helvetica"))
## Warning: Removed 1 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

p <- ggplot(health_indicators, mapping = aes(Hospital_bed_density, Death_density))
p + geom_point(color = "Red") +
  labs(x = "Hospital Beds per 100k People", y = "COVID19 Deaths per 100k Population") +
  ggtitle("Density of Hospital Beds and COVID19 Deaths") + 
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) +
  scale_x_continuous() +
  theme(text = element_text(family = "Helvetica"))

Using tiles- COVID19 Deaths

https://rstudio.github.io/leaflet/choropleths.html

library(leaflet)
library(RColorBrewer)

library(rgdal)
## Loading required package: sp
## rgdal: version: 1.5-18, (SVN revision 1082)
## Geospatial Data Abstraction Library extensions to R successfully loaded
## Loaded GDAL runtime: GDAL 3.1.1, released 2020/06/22
## Path to GDAL shared files: /Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Versions/4.0/Resources/library/rgdal/gdal
## GDAL binary built with GEOS: TRUE 
## Loaded PROJ runtime: Rel. 6.3.1, February 10th, 2020, [PJ_VERSION: 631]
## Path to PROJ shared files: /Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Versions/4.0/Resources/library/rgdal/proj
## Linking to sp version:1.4-4
## To mute warnings of possible GDAL/OSR exportToProj4() degradation,
## use options("rgdal_show_exportToProj4_warnings"="none") before loading rgdal.
world <- readOGR("TM_WORLD_BORDERS_SIMPL-0.3", "WorldData")
## OGR data source with driver: ESRI Shapefile 
## Source: "/Users/gennacampain/Desktop/Data Visualization/R Projects/RProjects/TM_WORLD_BORDERS_SIMPL-0.3", layer: "WorldData"
## with 246 features
## It has 21 fields
## Integer64 fields read as strings:  POP2005 Total_Coun Total_Co_1 FID_
mytext <- paste(
    "Country: ", world@data$NAME,"<br/>", 
    "Deaths per 100k People: ", world@data$COVID_19_D, "<br/>", 
    sep="") %>%
  lapply(htmltools::HTML)

m <- leaflet(world) %>%
addTiles() %>% addPolygons(stroke = FALSE, fillOpacity = 1, smoothFactor = 0.2, color = ~colorBin(c("#FFFFCC", "#FED976", "#FD8D3C", "#E31A1C", "#800026"), COVID_19_D, bins = 5, pretty = FALSE) (COVID_19_D), 
label = mytext)
m %>%
  addLegend(position = "bottomright", values = ~COVID_19_D, title = "COVID19 Deaths per 100k People", colors = c("#FFFFCC", "#FED976", "#FD8D3C", "#E31A1C", "#800026"), labels = c("0-19", "20-38", "39-58", "59-78", "79-98"))

Using Tiles- Health Expenditures

library(leaflet)
library(RColorBrewer)

mytext <- paste(
    "Country: ", world@data$NAME,"<br/>", 
    "Health Expenditures as % of GDP: ", world@data$Current__1, "<br/>", 
    sep="") %>%
  lapply(htmltools::HTML)

m <- leaflet(world) %>%
addTiles() %>% addPolygons(stroke = FALSE, fillOpacity = 1, smoothFactor = 0.2, color = ~colorBin(c("#FFFFCC", "#FED976", "#FD8D3C", "#E31A1C", "#800026"), Current__1, bins = 5, pretty = FALSE) (Current__1), 
label = mytext)
m %>%
  addLegend(position = "bottomright", values = ~Current__1, title = "Health Expenditures (% of GDP)", colors = c("#FFFFCC", "#FED976", "#FD8D3C", "#E31A1C", "#800026"), labels = c("No Data-3.40", "3.41-6.80", "6.81-10.20", "10.21-13.60", "13.61-17.1"))
